TOOLS : 

P : [object1.c][object2.c] -> AS -> [object1.o][object2.o][library.a] -> LD -> [executable]

as : translation of assembly code to object code

ld : combine several object files and libraries, resolves references, produces an ouput file

ar : creates and maintains groups of files combined into an archive (static librarie)

OBJECT :

executable : loader-readable form, meta-data + set of encoded instructions

object file : sequence of machine-code statements 

			executable
		 /
object1.o - object2.o
		 \
			library

shared libraries : group of sequences of machine-code statements to be linked at load-time or run-time

static libraries : group ofs sequences of machine-code statements to be linked at compile-time

exported/external/global/private/public


DIVERS :


flat namespaces vs two-level namespaces

compile-time | load-time | run-time

archive : undefined reference

meta-data of object files : 
	- header
	- code segment
	- data segment
	- read-only data segment
	- BSS segment
	- external definitions
	- relocation
	- dynamic linking
	- debugging


PRIMITIVES :

symbol : identifiers to enforce uniqueness of instance

symbol table : each identifiers is associated with meta-data informations

string table : strings to represent each symbol


MACH-O segments :

each Mach-O segment has a particular structure

LC_CODE_SIGNATURE : defines signature of binary

LC_DATA_IN_CODE : table of non instructions in code

LC_FUNCTION_STARTS : defines entry-point of executable

LC_LOAD_DYLIB : defines the name of dynamic loaded-library

LC_MAIN : defines main of a executable

LC_SOURCE_VERSION : defines the source version of program

LC_VERSION_MIN_MACOSX : defines the min macos x version

LC_UUID : defines a universally unique identifier to identify information in system

LC_LOAD_DYLINKER : specifies the dynamic linker to use

LC_DYSYMTAB : specifies additional symbol table info used by the dynamic linker

LC_DYLD_INFO_ONLY : specifies compressed dyld info only

LC_SEGMENT_64 : maps a 64-bit segment into the the given task address space
	_LINKEDIT : all structs created and maintened by the link editor

	_DATA : tradition UNIX data segment

	_TEXT : tradition UNIX text segment

	_PAGEZERO : the pagezero segment



Mach-o(5), stab(5), strip(1)


HACKS :

- auto-inspect against itself to accede syscall
- manipulate UUID to provoke collision
